cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.CE

The paper deals with the analysis of brain networks using diffusion MRI data. The methods used involve graph theory and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of large-scale parallel algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves image processing techniques, which could place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves the use of statistical measures, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
